ag=\"cm_cr_getr_d_rvw_rvwer\" data-reviews-state-param=\"{&quot;pageNumber&quot;:&quot;1&quot;,&quot;reviewerType&quot;:&quot;avp_only_reviews&quot;}\" class=\"a-link-normal\" href=\"/Natures-Calling-Cat-Litter-pack/product-reviews/B00EO08PAO/ref=cm_cr_getr_d_rvw_rvwer?ie=UTF8&reviewerType=avp_only_reviews&pageSize=10&sortBy=recent\"><span data-hook=\"avp-badge\" class=\"a-size-mini a-color-state a-text-bold\">Verified Purchase</span></a></span></div><div class=\"a-row review-data\"><span data-hook=\"review-body\" class=\"a-size-base review-text\">After reading all the other reviews on Amazon, I decided to try this product as I had not been happy with any of the other litters we had tried.  I have three cats and was using wood pellet cat litter as I didn't like the smell of other litters.  I tried the worlds best and can't believe its performance.  The litter trays are much easier to maintain now, there are minimal odour problems, and the cats started using it straight away with no issues.  The litter is organic matter, and has a pleasant smell.  It is a fine granular structure and absorbs moisture and odour very quickly. The clumps are then easily removed leaving behind clean fresh litter for the cats.  I've not tried flushing the litter, but you can do if required.  Have been using it for several months now and there is no way I would change back, its definitely worth paying that bit extra and as you don't use as much emptying and refilling the trays, its probably more economical in the long run</span></div><div class=\"a-row a-spacing-top-small review-comments comments-for-RYH4LVR7QYJQ4\"><div data-reftag=\"cm_cr_getr_d_cmt_opn\" aria-live=\"polite\" data-a-expander-name=\"review_comment_expander\" class=\"a-row a-expander-container a-expander-inline-container\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" data-action=\"a-expander-toggle\" class=\"a-expander-header a-declarative a-expander-inline-header a-link-expander\" data-a-expander-toggle=\"{&quot;allowLinkDefault&quot;:t